The paper is about Automated Program Repair (APR), which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions machine learning and dimensionality reduction, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses specific features of the buggy part of the program, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the potential for e-APR to be integrated into repair infrastructures and repair bots, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze data, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
